visional managers. However, decentralisation may also result in a loss of central control, incongruence of goals and strategies, and increased information requirements.\",9\n1185,\"\"\"DIVISIONAL PERFORMANCE MEASURES\"\"\",\"\"\"Divisional performance measures should be goal-congruent, timely, and controllable by the divisional manager. The most suitable measures depend on whether the business unit is a cost, profit, or investment centre.\"\"\",3\n1151,\"\"\"DIVISIONAL PERFORMANCE EVALUATION\"\"\",The Divisional Performance Evaluation involves assessing the performance of different business units or divisions within an organization. This process includes measuring and controlling divisional performance and implementing fair transfer pricing. The use of fair transfer prices is crucial to objectively assess and motivate divisional performance.,2\n1157,\"\"\"BENEFITS OF DECENTRALISATION\"\"\",\"\"\"Benefits of decentralisation include allowing senior management to concentrate on strategy, faster decision-making, better decision-making by specialist managers, increased motivation, training and career progression for divisional managers, and tax advantages.\"\"\",1\n1159,\"\"\"CONDITIONS FOR SUCCESSFUL DECENTRALISATION\"\"\",\"\"\"Conditions for successful decentralisation include carefully designed performance evaluation systems, having several separate business activities, central policies to integrate and control, and ensuring divisions are independent from each other.\"\"\",1\n1154,\"\"\"COST CENTRES\"\"\",\"\"\"Cost centres are business units where managers are responsible for decisions about costs.\"\"\",1\n1153,\"\"\"REVENUE CENTRES\"\"\",\"\"\"Revenue centres are business units where managers are responsible for decisions about revenue generation, usually including selling costs.\"\"\",1\n1155,\"\"\"PROFIT CENTRES\"\"\",\"\"\"Profit centres are business units where managers are responsible for decisions about both costs and revenues.\"\"\",1\n1156,\"\"\"INVESTMENT CENTRES\"\"\",\"\"\"Investment centres are business units where managers are responsible for decisions about costs, revenues, and asset investments.\"\"\",1\n1158,\"\"\"PROBLEMS OF DECENTRALISATION\"\"\",\"\"\"Problems of decentralisation include lack of goal congruence, increased information requirements, lost economies of scale, and loss of central control.\"\"\",1\n1171,\"\"\"GOAL CONGRUENCE\"\"\",\"\"\"Goal congruence\"\" ensures that transfer prices encourage divisional managers to make decisions in the best interests of the organization as a whole. It is the alignment of individual or divisional objectives with the overall objectives of the organization. Specifically, goal congruence refers to the alignment of divisional managers' decisions with the organization's primary objective of maximizing shareholders' wealth.\",4\n1193,\"\"\"SUPPLYING DIVISION PERSPECTIVE\"\"\",\"\"\"The supplying division will accept a minimum transfer price equal to the marginal (variable) cost plus the opportunity cost.\"\"\",3\n1189,\"\"\"OBJECTIVES OF TRANSFER PRICING\"\"\",\"\"\"The objectives of transfer pricing are goal congruence, divisional autonomy, and divisional performance evaluation.\"\"\",2\n1192,\"\"\"DIVISIONAL AUTONOMY\"\"\",\"\"\"Divisional autonomy refers to the freedom of divisional managers to make their own decisions, which can improve motivation but may lead to imbalanced transfer pricing.\"\"\",1\n1170,\"\"\"INVESTMENT DECISIONS\"\"\",\"\"\"Investment decisions involve determining whether the divisional managers would accept the project available to their respective divisions based on ROI.\"\"\",2\n1190,\"\"\"EXAMPLE OF GOAL CONGRUENCE\"\"\",\"\"\"EXAMPLE OF GOAL CONGRUENCE\"\"\n\nABC Consulting, a firm with offices in several major cities, provides an example of goal congruence in transfer pricing. This occurs when consultants in one office make decisions that benefit the entire organization. However, there was an instance where ABC Consulting's internal transfer pricing led to a decision that was advantageous for the Budapest office but not for the overall company, illustrating goal incongruence. This highlights the importance of aligning individual office goals with the broader objectives of the company to achieve overall success.\",1\n1194,\"\"\"SCENARIO 1 - OPPORTUNITY COST IS ZERO\"\"\",\"\"\"When there is no external market or there is spare capacity, the opportunity cost is zero, and the minimum transfer price is the marginal cost.\"\"\",2\n1196,\"\"\"SCENARIO 2 - OPPORTUNITY COST ARISES\"\"\",\"\"\"An opportunity cost arises when an internal sale sacrifices an external sale, and the supplying division operates at full capacity.\"\"\",2\n1187,\"\"\"TRACEABLE PROFIT\"\"\",\"\"\"Traceable profit is the profit after charging divisional costs outside the manager's control.\"\"\",1\n1168,\"\"\"DIVISION Y\"\"\",\"\"\"Division Y is another division being evaluated for potential projects, with a current ROI of 9%.\"\"\",1\n1195,\"\"\"QUIZ: NO OPPORTUNITY COST\"\"\",\"\"\"This quiz involves calculating the minimum transfer price when there is no opportunity cost and determining the actions of divisions in such a scenario.\"\"\",1\n1197,\"\"\"QUIZ: WITH OPPORTUNITY COST\"\"\",\"\"\"This quiz involves determining the minimum transfer price when there is an opportunity cost and evaluating the actions of divisions in such a scenario.\"\"\",1\n\n\n-----Relationships-----\nhuman_readable_id,source,target,description,rank\n1189,\"\"\"TRANSFER PRICING\"\"\",\"\"\"DIVISION B\"\"\",\"\"\"Transfer pricing affects Division B as it determines the revenue Division B earns from selling fittings to Division A.\"\"\",15\n1150,\"\"\"DECENTRALISATION\"\"\",\"\"\"DIVISIONAL PERFORMANCE MEASURES\"\"\",\"\"\"Decentralisation impacts the effectiveness of Divisional Performance Measures.\"\"\",12\n1141,\"\"\"DIVISIONAL PERFORMANCE EVALUATION\"\"\",\"\"\"DECENTRALISATION\"\"\",\"\"\"Divisional Performance Evaluation is closely related to decentralisation as it involves assessing the performance of decentralised business units.\"\"\",11\n1147,\"\"\"DECENTRALISATION\"\"\",\"\"\"BENEFITS OF DECENTRALISATION\"\"\",\"\"\"Decentralisation provides several benefits including strategic focus for senior management and faster decision-making.\"\"\",10\n1149,\"\"\"DECENTRALISATION\"\"\",\"\"\"CONDITIONS FOR SUCCESSFUL DECENTRALISATION\"\"\",\"\"\"Successful decentralisation requires carefully designed performance evaluation systems and central policies to integrate and control.\"\"\",10\n1144,\"\"\"DECENTRALISATION\"\"\",\"\"\"COST CENTRES\"\"\",\"\"\"Cost centres are a type of business unit created under decentralisation.\"\"\",10\n1143,\"\"\"DECENTRALISATION\"\"\",\"\"\"REVENUE CENTRES\"\"\",\"\"\"Revenue centres are a type of business unit created under decentralisation.\"\"\",10\n1145,\"\"\"DECENTRALISATION\"\"\",\"\"\"PROFIT CENTRES\"\"\",\"\"\"Profit centres are a type of business unit created under decentralisation.\"\"\",10\n1146,\"\"\"DECENTRALISATION\"\"\",\"\"\"INVESTMENT CENTRES\"\"\",\"\"\"Investment centres are a type of business unit created under decentralisation.\"\"\",10\n1148,\"\"\"DECENTRALISATION\"\"\",\"\"\"PROBLEMS OF DECENTRALISATION\"\"\",\"\"\"Decentralisation can lead to problems such as lack of goal congruence and increased information requirements.\"\"\",10\n1158,\"\"\"GOAL CONGRUENCE\"\"\",\"\"\"TRANSFER PRICING\"\"\",\"\"\"Achieving goal congruence is a primary objective of a transfer pricing system.\"\"\",10\n1188,\"\"\"TRANSFER PRICING\"\"\",\"\"\"SUPPLYING DIVISION PERSPECTIVE\"\"\",\"\"\"The supplying division's perspective on transfer pricing includes considering marginal cost and opportunity cost.\"\"\",9\n1142,\"\"\"DIVISIONAL PERFORMANCE EVALUATION\"\"\",\"\"\"TRANSFER PRICING\"\"\",\"\"\"Transfer prices should be fair to allow objective assessment of divisional performance.\"\"\",8\n1186,\"\"\"TRANSFER PRICING\"\"\",\"\"\"OBJECTIVES OF TRANSFER PRICING\"\"\",\"\"\"Transfer Pri